{
  "texts": [
    "With pathologist interpretation, they can highlight morphologic associations between outcome variables and offer insights into the spatial relationship of image features among classes.Gradient-based pixel attribution approaches highlight the pixels in an image that were relevant for a given neural network model prediction.",
    "These attribution heatmaps, or saliency maps, can be calculated through a variety of provided methods, including Grad-CAM [64], vanilla gradients [65], integrated gradients (and variations thereof) [66], and XRAI [67].",
    "Saliency maps can be displayed as raw heatmaps or as overlays onto the associated image.",
    "Utility functions are included for rapid comparison between different saliency map methods.",
    "Saliency maps can also be interactively viewed for WSIs in real-time using Slideflow Studio."
  ]
}